#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rmd_calculator.html:280
msgid "What is a Required Minimum Distribution?"
msgstr "Vad är en obligatorisk minimidistribution?"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rmd_calculator.html:281
msgid ""
"A Required Minimum Distribution (RMD) is the minimum amount you must "
"withdraw from your retirement account each year once you reach a certain "
"age. The IRS requires these withdrawals to ensure you pay taxes on your tax-"
"deferred retirement savings."
msgstr ""
"En Required Minimum Distribution (RMD) är det lägsta belopp du måste ta ut "
"från ditt pensionskonto varje år när du når en viss ålder. IRS kräver dessa "
"uttag för att säkerställa att du betalar skatt på ditt skatteuppskjutna "
"pensionssparande."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rmd_calculator.html:287
msgid "Traditional IRAs require RMDs"
msgstr "Traditionella IRA kräver RMD"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rmd_calculator.html:293
msgid "401(k) and 403(b) plans require RMDs"
msgstr "401(k) och 403(b) planer kräver RMDs"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rmd_calculator.html:299
msgid "Roth IRAs do NOT require RMDs during your lifetime"
msgstr "Roth IRA kräver INTE RMD under din livstid"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rmd_calculator.html:306
msgid "RMD Penalties"
msgstr "RMD-straff"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rmd_calculator.html:308
#, python-format
msgid "25%% Penalty for Missing RMDs"
msgstr "25 %% straff för saknade RMD"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rmd_calculator.html:309
#, python-format
msgid ""
"If you don't take your full RMD by the deadline, you'll owe a 25%% excise "
"tax on the amount not withdrawn. This can be reduced to 10%% if corrected "
"promptly."
msgstr ""
"Om du inte tar ut din fulla RMD inom deadline, är du skyldig 25 % i "
"punktskatt på det belopp som inte har tagits ut. Detta kan reduceras till 10"
" %% om det korrigeras omgående."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rmd_calculator.html:313
msgid "Deadline"
msgstr "Tidsfrist"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rmd_calculator.html:314
msgid ""
"RMDs must be taken by December 31st each year. First-year RMDs can be "
"delayed until April 1st of the following year (but you'll need to take two "
"RMDs that year)."
msgstr ""
"RMD måste tas senast den 31 december varje år. RMD för första året kan "
"skjutas upp till den 1 april följande år (men du måste ta två RMD det året)."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rmd_calculator.html:326
msgid "How is my RMD calculated?"
msgstr "Hur beräknas min RMD?"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rmd_calculator.html:331
msgid ""
"Your RMD is calculated by dividing your prior year-end account balance by "
"your life expectancy factor from the IRS Uniform Lifetime Table. For "
"example, if your balance was $500,000 and your factor is 26.5, your RMD "
"would be $18,868."
msgstr ""
"Din RMD beräknas genom att dividera ditt föregående årsbokslut med din "
"förväntade livslängdsfaktor från IRS Uniform Lifetime Table. Till exempel, "
"om ditt saldo var 500 000 $ och din faktor är 26,5, skulle din RMD vara 18 "
"868 $."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rmd_calculator.html:336
msgid "Can I withdraw more than my RMD?"
msgstr "Kan jag ta ut mer än min RMD?"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rmd_calculator.html:341
msgid ""
"Yes! The RMD is the minimum you must withdraw. You can always take more. "
"However, any excess cannot be applied to future years' RMDs. Extra "
"withdrawals will be taxed as ordinary income."
msgstr ""
"Ja! RMD är det minsta du måste ta ut. Du kan alltid ta mer. Eventuellt "
"överskott kan dock inte tillämpas på framtida års RMD. Extra uttag kommer "
"att beskattas som vanlig inkomst."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rmd_calculator.html:346
msgid "What if I have multiple IRAs?"
msgstr "Vad händer om jag har flera IRA?"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/rmd_calculator.html:351
msgid ""
"You must calculate RMDs separately for each Traditional IRA you own. "
"However, you can take the total amount from any one or combination of your "
"IRAs. 401(k) RMDs must be taken from each account separately."
msgstr ""
"Du måste beräkna RMDs separat för varje traditionell IRA du äger. Du kan "
"dock ta det totala beloppet från vilken som helst eller kombination av dina "
"IRA. 401(k) RMD måste tas från varje konto separat."

